<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-26T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-26T23:00:00-05:00" n="1228" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1228">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2912.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American Consul at Ciudad
                                    Juárez</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-26T23:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 26, 1912—11 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>You will immediately, informally, and unofficially advise Campa that
                            under no circumstances must there be any firing into American territory,
                            and admonish him that any violation of this warning will almost
                            certainly lead to consequences which it is to the interest of all true
                            Mexican patriots to avoid. You will impress upon Campa the very great
                            seriousness of the situation and the much-to-be-deplored results which
                            would follow his failure to heed this warning. You will convey a like
                            message officially to the commanding officer of the Federal troops.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>